Retired head of the African Independent Pentecostal Church of Africa Archbishop Amos Kabuthu has expressed his commitment to ensure that the church remains unified.He said efforts have been made to reach out the splinter groups which ordained Bishop Julius Njoroge as the new archbishop recently.He maintained that he retired recently and handed over the mantle of the church to Bishop Fredrick Wang&rsquo;ombe who will head the church onwards.Kabuthu however lashed out unto some church officials who have strong behind forces connections with State House whom he said has led to wrangles of the church.